    "body": "Thanks for posting this.\r\n\r\nSo another approach would be being able to specify address-password pairs in the password file, doing away with the `--unlock` flag altogether:\r\n\r\n```\r\n0x345768767453453453:mypassw0rd\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut as @ligi says, just the \"did you forget\" addon would also have saved a lot of time. Actually even just stating `authentication needed: --password or --unlock` would make it clear those are flags, reducing ambiguity (which, admittedly, stemmed from me being a newbie).",
